  "commentary": "With SPX at 6576 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.6B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+2.3B), dealers are currently in neutral territory but primed for amplification in either direction. The massive negative GEX walls stacked below (6500, 6400, 6570, 6575) create a dangerous setup where any downside momentum will force dealers to sell aggressively, while a push above 6600 will trigger dealer selling that could cap upside. The gex_surge event combined with extreme 1-min (-20%) and 5-min (+35%) GEX volatility suggests we're at an inflection point where the next directional move will be amplified by dealer flow.\n\nBottom line: expect explosive moves in whichever direction we break from this 6500-6600 zone.",
